    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An inductively coupled plasma (ICP) is a type of high-temperature plasma (ionized gas) source generated by electric currents produced by electromagnetic induction. It is used to determine elemental content of materials in ICP spectrometry.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
